	<ShibuiContent id="public-record-data-scrapper.the-challenge-of-50-state-scale.p1">
		<span slot="entry">
			<p>I directed the architecture of a platform that automates public record extraction across all 50 US states. Each state has its own UCC filing system with different interfaces and anti-scraping measures — a human researcher covers two or three states per day. I replaced that with 60+ autonomous agents extracting filings continuously, enriching them with multi-source intelligence, and delivering scored leads through a full React application.</p>
		</span>
		<span slot="elevated">
			<p>
				Public record data in the United States is structurally fragmented. Each state maintains
				its own <ShibuiTerm term="Uniform Commercial Code" definition="A standardized set of laws governing commercial transactions in the US, including UCC-1 financing statements that signal active business lending" /> (UCC) filing system, often with proprietary interfaces,
				inconsistent data schemas, and aggressive anti-scraping measures. The Merchant Cash
				Advance (MCA) industry — a multi-billion-dollar alternative lending sector serving small
				and mid-size businesses — depends on these filings as the single most reliable signal
				that a business has active financing and may need additional capital. Yet a broker trying
				to prospect across all fifty states faces compounding costs: each Secretary of State
				portal requires separate navigation, often with CAPTCHAs, session limits, or
				bulk-download restrictions. A human researcher might cover two to three states per day.
				<Cite
					id={1}
					author="Trask, Stephen"
					title="The High Cost of Data Fragmentation"
					source="Journal of Digital Commerce"
					year={2022}
				/> I directed the architecture of a platform that replaces this manual fragmentation with
				an automated, AI-driven pipeline: sixty-plus autonomous agents extracting UCC filings
				continuously across all fifty states, enriching them with multi-source intelligence, and
				delivering scored, outreach-ready leads through a full-featured React application with
				integrated CRM, compliance tooling, and communications infrastructure.
			</p>
		</span>
	</ShibuiContent>
	<button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper &#8594;</button>

